{{Infobox person | name = Abdeslam Ahizoune | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date ={{Birth date and age|1955|04|20}} | birth_place = [[Tiflet]], [[Morocco]]<ref name=telquel>{{cite web |url=http://www.telquel-online.com/440/couverture_440.shtml |title=Abdeslam Ahizoune. Ombres et lumières d’une success story |publisher=Telquel |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110807094133/http://www.telquel-online.com/440/couverture_440.shtml |archive-date=2011-08-07 |accessdate=23 November 2011 |dead-url=no |df= }}</ref> | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | nationality = [[Morocco|Moroccan]] | other_names = | known_for = | occupation = Businessman, Politician }} '''Abdeslam Ahizoune''' (born 20 April 1955 in [[Tiflet]], [[Morocco]])<ref name=telquel/> is the [[Chairman]] and Chief Executive Officer of [[Maroc Telecom]]; the [[:Category:Telecommunications companies of Morocco|Moroccan telecommunications company]], and as such is a member of the Management Board of [[Vivendi]] corporation, MT's parent company.
== Biography == Abdeslam Ahizoune graduated from l’[[École Nationale Supérieure des Télécommunications de Paris]] in 1977.<ref>[http://corporate-executives.com/abdeslamahizoune/ Abdeslam Ahizoune] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130831154930/http://corporate-executives.com/abdeslamahizoune/ |date=2013-08-31 }}, ''Corporate Executives''</ref>
Since December 2006, Ahizoune is the [[Chairman]] of the [[Fédération Royale Marocaine d’Athlétisme]], [[Morocco]]'s [[Athletics (track and field)|Athletics]] governing body and member of [[Royal institute of the Amazigh culture]].
