{{Infobox company | name = DVA Group | logo = DVA logo.png | type = [[GmbH]] | traded_as = | founder = | foundation = [[1968]] | location = [[Hamburg]], [[Germany]] | area_served = Worldwide | key_people = {{Plainlist| * [[Matthias Damm]] {{small|(CEO)}} }} | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | assets = | equity = | num_employees = 300+ | industry = {{ubl|[[Chemical industry|Chemicals]]}} | products = {{ubl|[[Agrochemicals]]|[[List of life sciences|Life sciences]]|[[Pharmaceutical industry|Pharmaceuticals]]|[[Plastics]]|[[Coatings]]}} | homepage = [https://www.dva.com/ www.dva.com] | subsid = | parent = }} '''DVA''' is a [[Germany|German]] [[multinational corporation|multinational]] agrochemicals, pharmaceutical, life sciences and plastics company<ref>[https://www.bloomberg.com/profiles/companies/9866203Z:GR-dva-group DVA Group] Bloomberg.com</ref> with subsidiaries in more than 20 countries worldwide. The headquarter of the family-owned company is in [[Hamburg]], [[Germany]] and was established in [[1968]].
== Presentation == [[File:DVA Building.png|thumb|DVA Headquarters, Hamburg, Germany]] DVA was founded in [[1968]] as a ship-broker in [[Hamburg]], Germany. Then, the company evolved into a specialist for integrated services in the fields of marketing, research & development and distribution. Today DVA Group operate in three divisions: * DVA Agro: [[Crop protection]] and Plant Nutrition * DVA Plastics: Plastics for Engineering * DVA Health & Nutrition: Food-Additives, Pharmaceutical Raw Material and Veterinary Products
== History == * 1968 : Foundation of DVA in Hamburg, Germany. * 1972 : Horst Damm joins the company and establishes steel trading activities with Southeast Asia. * 1980 : Opening of the first overseas office of DVA in Bejing. * 1993 : DVA branches out into the field of crop protection products<ref>[https://rockemkenya.com/dva-agro-gmbh-hamburg-germany/ DVA Agro GmbH, Hamburg, Germany] Rockem Kenya</ref>. * 2001 : Matthias Damm becomes CEO of the company. * 2003 : DVA enters into the markets of [[Brazil]]<ref>[https://www.en.investe.sp.gov.br/news/post/brazil-gains-weigh-in-businesses-of-german-dva/ Brazil gains weigh in businesses of German DVA] Investe.sp.gov.br</ref><ref>[http://news.agropages.com/News/NewsDetail---4537.htm United Phosphorus acquires majority stake in DVA Agro Brazil] Agropages.com</ref>., [[Colombia]] and [[India]]. * 2010 : DVA expands the business with crop protection products into Africa. * 2018 : DVA’s new production facilities go on stream in [[Mexico]] and [[Argentina]]. DVA presents its new Brand Identity.
