'''Henrik Andenæs''' (born 17 September 1950) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] businessperson.

He was born in Oslo, and took the [[siviløkonom|siv.øk.]] degree at the [[Norwegian School of Economics]] in 1975. He worked in the United States for [[Kreditkassen]] from 1985 to 1987, was vice chief executive in [[Ringnes]] from 1987 to 1990, then chief executive of [[LOOC]] from 1990 to 1994. From 1994 to 1997 he worked in [[Singapore]] for the [[Orkla Group]], and in October 1998 he was hired as information director in [[Norsk Hydro]].<ref name=ntb>{{cite news|title=Henrik Andenæs 50 år 17. september|agency=[[Norwegian News Agency]]|date=25 August 2000|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

He was later the chief executive of ''Troms Fylkes Dampskipsselskap'' when it merged with ''Ofotens og Vesteraalens Dampskibsselskab'' in 2006 to form the [[Hurtigruten Group]]. He became vice chief executive, but already in April 2006 he advanced to chief executive.<ref>{{cite news|title=OVDS og TFDS blir Hurtigruten Group|agency=[[Norwegian News Agency]]|date=2 December 2005|language=Norwegian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Hurtigruten skifter sjef|agency=[[Norwegian News Agency]]|date=18 April 2006|language=Norwegian}}</ref> In April 2007 Andenæs resigned here.<ref>{{cite news|title=Henrik Andenæs forlater Hurtigruten|agency=[[Norwegian News Agency]]|date=25 April 2007|language=Norwegian}}</ref> In December 2007 he was selected as chairman of the [[41st Chess Olympiad]] in [[Tromsø]], which was in the bidding process at the time.<ref>{{cite news|title=Skal styre sjakk-kampen|author=Thuen, Ingrid|work=[[Bladet Tromsø]]|date=27 December 2007|language=Norwegian}}</ref> In June 2008 he became chairman of Ludwig Mack, the [[holding company]] of [[Macks Ølbryggeri]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Andenæs ny styreleder|author=Sæbbe, Linda Vaeng|work=[[Nordlys]]|date=17 June 2008|page=20|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

Following the [[1994 Winter Olympics]] he was decorated as a Knight, First Class of the [[Order of St. Olav]] together with LOOC's vice chief executive [[Petter Rønningen]].<ref>{{cite news|title=St. Olav til Heiberg, Rønningen og Andenæs|agency=[[Norwegian News Agency]]|date=26 February 1994|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

