{{for|other people called John Thomson Mason|John Thomson Mason (disambiguation)}} {{use dmy dates | date = April 2013}} {{Infobox Politician |name= John Thomson Mason |image= |caption= |office= [[Attorney General of Maryland]] |term_start= 1806 |term_end= 1806 |birth_date= {{Birth date|1765|03|15|df=yes}} |birth_place= [[Chopawamsic (plantation)|Chopawamsic]], [[Stafford County, Virginia|Stafford County]], [[Colony of Virginia]] | death_date ={{Death date and age|1824|12|10|1765|03|15|df=yes}} | death_place = |predecessor= [[William Pinkney]] |successor = [[John Johnson Sr.]] | party = | spouse = Elizabeth Beltzhoover | children = 7, including [[John Thomson Mason Jr.]] | profession= [[Lawyer|Attorney]] | website = | footnotes = | residence = [[Montpelier (Clear Spring, Maryland)|Montpelier]], [[Clear Spring, Maryland|Clear Spring]], [[Maryland]] }} '''John Thomson Mason''' (15 March 1765 &ndash; 10 December 1824)<ref name=GH>{{cite web | url=http://www.gunstonhall.org/masonweb/p26.htm#i1295 | title=John Thomson Mason | date=| accessdate=2008-02-15 | publisher=Gunston Hall | author=Gunston Hall |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080211141639/http://www.gunstonhall.org/masonweb/p26.htm#i1295 <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2008-02-11}}</ref><ref name=PG>{{cite web | url=http://politicalgraveyard.com/families/10855.html | title=Mason family of Virginia | date= June 16, 2008| accessdate=2009-03-07 | publisher=The Political Graveyard | author=The Political Graveyard}}</ref> was an American lawyer and [[Attorney General of Maryland]] in 1806.<ref name=PG/>
==Early life== Mason was born on 15 March 1765 at [[Chopawamsic (plantation)|Chopawamsic]] in [[Stafford County, Virginia]].<ref name=GH/><ref name=PG/> He was the third child and youngest son of [[Thomson Mason]] and his wife Mary King Barnes.<ref name=GH/>
==Education and career== Mason attained high rank at the bar,<ref name=CDA>{{cite book| last = [[The Colonial Dames of America]] | first = | title =Ancestral Records and Portraits: A Compilation from the Archives of Chapter I, the Colonial Dames of America | publisher =Grafton Press | year= 1910 | location =[[Boston]], [[Massachusetts]] | pages=808}}</ref> but twice declined the office of [[United States Attorney General]] when it was offered by [[President of the United States|Presidents]] [[Thomas Jefferson]] and [[James Madison]].<ref name=CDA/> Mason ran for one of [[List of United States Senators from Maryland|Maryland]]'s seats in the [[United States Senate]], but lost.<ref name=CDA/> He then served as [[Attorney General of Maryland]] in 1806.<ref name=PG/>
==Marriages and children== Mason married Elizabeth Beltzhoover in 1797.<ref name=GH/><ref name=PG/> He and Elizabeth had seven children:<ref name=GH/><ref name=PG/>
*Mary Barnes Mason Winter (c. 1800&ndash;11 May 1844)<ref name=GH/> *Elizabeth Ann Armistead Thomson Mason Wharton (4 April 1803&ndash;20 January 1857)<ref name=GH/> *Abram Barnes Mason Barnes (21 October 1807&ndash;10 April 1863)<ref name=GH/> *Melchior Beltzhoover Mason (born 3 October 1812)<ref name=GH/> *[[John Thomson Mason, Jr.]] (9 May 1815&ndash;28 March 1873)<ref name=GH/> *Thomson Mason (15 July 1818&ndash;1848)<ref name=GH/> *Virginia Wallace Mason (16 April 1820&ndash;6 October 1858)<ref name=GH/>
==Later life== Mason died on 10 December 1824 at the age of 59.<ref name=GH/> Mason was interred at his [[Montpelier (Clear Spring, Maryland)|Montpelier]] estate in [[Clear Spring, Maryland|Clear Spring]], Maryland.<ref name=MW>{{cite book |title=Maryland: A Guide to the Old Line State |last=Federal Writers' Project |first= |authorlink= |coauthors= |year= |publisher=US History Publishers |location= |isbn=1-60354-019-9 |page= |pages= |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=K6BlU1wPV7oC }}</ref>
==Relations== John Thomson Mason was a nephew of [[George Mason]] (1725&ndash;1792);<ref name=GH/> son of [[Thomson Mason]] (1733&ndash;1785);<ref name=GH/> brother of [[Stevens Thomson Mason (Virginia)|Stevens Thomson Mason]] (1760&ndash;1803);<ref name=GH/> half-brother of [[William Temple Thomson Mason]] (1782&ndash;1862);<ref name=GH/> first cousin of [[George Mason V]] (1753&ndash;1796);<ref name=GH/> first cousin once removed of [[Thomson Francis Mason]] (1785&ndash;1838), [[George Mason VI]] (1786&ndash;1834), [[Richard Barnes Mason]] (1797&ndash;1850), and [[James Murray Mason]] (1798&ndash;1871);<ref name=GH/> uncle of [[Armistead Thomson Mason]] (1787&ndash;1819) and [[John Thomson Mason (1787–1850)|John Thomson Mason]] (1787&ndash;1850);<ref name=GH/> father of [[John Thomson Mason Jr.]] (1815&ndash;1873);<ref name=GH/> and great uncle of [[Stevens T. Mason|Stevens Thomson Mason]] (1811&ndash;1843).<ref name=GH/>
